ZH: 如果你说穿了他的借口，他就没有任何道理了。
EN: If you see through his excuse, he won't have any reason left.

ZH: 她说穿了我为什么迟到的借口。
EN: She saw through my excuse for being late.

ZH: 我无法说穿他的真实动机。
EN: I couldn't see through his true motives.

ZH: 如果你说穿了他的谎言，他将很尴尬。
EN: If you expose his lies, he will be embarrassed.

ZH: 不要以为你能说穿我内心的想法。
EN: Don't think you can read my thoughts and see through me.

ZH: 他很聪明，不容易被人说穿。
EN: He is very clever and not easily seen through.

ZH: 她总是能说穿他人的意图，非常敏锐。
EN: She can always see through people's intentions, very sharp.

ZH: 我们需要一个能说穿虚伪人的人来担任这个角色。
EN: We need someone who can see through hypocritical people to play this role.

ZH: 我的朋友总是能说穿我心中的烦恼。
EN: My friend can always see through my troubles.

ZH: 他是个谁都无法说穿的人，神秘得很。
EN: He is someone who cannot be seen through, very mysterious.

ZH: 他的手法太明显，很容易被人说穿。
EN: His technique is too obvious, easily seen through.

ZH: 如果你继续这样，我会说穿你的计划。
EN: If you keep doing this, I will expose your plan.

ZH: 我能够说穿别人的谎言。
EN: I can see through other people's lies.

ZH: 她很容易被别人说穿，不善于隐藏真实感情。
EN: She is easily seen through, not good at hiding true emotions.

